1 AN ACT relating to responsible gambling.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 230 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) Any track licensed by the corporation to conduct live horse racing or races
6 previously run shall implement a program to promote responsible gambling by its
7 patrons and provide details of the same to the corporation. At a minimum, the
8 program shall require:
9 (a) Posting in a conspicuous location, in every place where pari-mutuel
10 wagering on historical horse racing is conducted, a sign that bears a toll-
11 free telephone number approved by the Kentucky Council on Problem
12 Gambling or other organization that provides assistance to problem
13 gamblers;
14 (b) Providing informational leaflets or other similar materials on its licensed
15 premises on the dangers associated with problem gambling;
16 (c) Including in the licensee's promotional and marketing materials
17 information on problem gambling and organizations that provide assistance
18 to problem gamblers;
19 (d) Routine auditing of patron activity to identify patrons who have suffered
20 significant financial losses in repeated visits to its licensed premises and
21 providing such patrons with information on organizations that provide
22 assistance to problem gamblers;
23 (e) Training for employees at licensed tracks that also hold a license issued
24 under KRS 243.265 to identify patrons who have consumed excessive
25 amounts of alcohol to prevent such patrons from continuing to engage in
26 wagering activity while impaired;
27 (f) Forming a partnership with the Kentucky Council on Problem Gambling,
